# Administrative Gravity
## Definition
The cumulative administrative responsibilities that divert an educator's attention away from direct teaching, mentorship, scholarship, and artistic practice.
## Context
Administrative Gravity serves as one of the foundational concepts of the Educator Intelligence Platform. Rather than describing any single task, it characterizes the collective effect of numerous administrative responsibilities on an educator's attention and available cognitive resources.
## Design Implications
The platform should minimize unnecessary context switching, preserve task continuity, and reduce friction between administrative work and instructional practice.
